animal.description:
Meet Rebekah! She's a 3yo spayed Lab-mix. Rebekah just came to Wisconsin from Oklahoma so we're just getting to know her.  She is unbelievably sweet and gentle but quite shy. She would benefit greatly from another dog in the home for cues and to help build her confidence. Even though loud noises and sudden movements startle her she is still sweet as can be and follows her 4yo human foster sister everywhere. She is quickly learning that cuddles & pets are awesome and she gives the cutest little kisses. The resident cats don't phase her at all; she pays them no attention. I have to physically put her into the crate because she's not used to it but doesn't whine or cry once she's in it. No potty accidents so far!

If you would like to be considered as a potential adopter for one of our great dogs, please go to our website- www.luckymuttsrescue.org and submit an application. Our application process includes landlord approval and vet checks. Please make sure all of your information is current and accurate, including a valid email address and phone numbers. Inaccuracies and/or incomplete data will delay and/or cancel your application.  We strive to process all applications in a timely manner, but with the high volume of applications we are receiving, it is taking anywhere from 1-3 weeks.  You may be contacted via email if there are concerns or questions.  Once all of your information is reviewed and if your application is approved, you will be notified via email.  Submitting an application and receiving an approval does not guarantee you will be adopting the dog you applied for.  Once you move to the meet and greet process, you will be contacted by the foster family to further discuss the dog, and answer questions you may have, and if applicable, a meet and greet will be set up at our adoption center.   Meet and greets are only set up with approved applicants, and we require all members in the household to be present, as well as any current dogs in the home. 

Current Adoption Fees Are:
$400+tax for puppies to 3 years old
$350+tax for ages 4-7
$250+tax for ages 8 and up
Bonded pairs vary

The adoption fee covers spay/neuter, up to date age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, general deworming, heartworm test, (if over 6  months) and a certified veterinary inspection. Please be aware, listed dog breeds are based on information provided and cannot be guaranteed.  Submitting an application for a particular dog does not guarantee that you will be the applicant chosen, we receive several applications for each dog. Our adopters are picked based on the needs of the dog, and the home we feel with best fit based on your responses to our application, vet information and landlord requirements.   Approved applicants not chosen for the dog you applied for, will be in active status for a period of six months.  We encourage you to watch Petfinder, Facebook and our website for upcoming dogs.  Should you see a dog that interests you, please send us a Facebook message or an email with your approval number.  Please be patient with us, as Lucky Mutts Rescue is run strictly by volunteers and many of us work full time jobs, have families and also foster dogs. Thank you for considering Lucky Mutts Rescue for your next furry family member!

animal.description:
EXPERIENCED SPECIAL NEEDS FOSTER OR ADOPTER REQUIRED
This little special needs Chiweenie is looking for a foster home. He suffered an injury due to neglect which caused permanent damage to his back legs. When we rescued him he was living in a home that was not equipped to help him with his disability. He was left in an ill-fitted wheelchair that actually caused more damage to his legs. Since he has been with us, he is going to hydrotherapy sessions, getting laser treatments weekly and he has even started to take several steps in a row on his daily walks. He is able to stand on his own and we think as he continues to get stronger he will be able to walk even further. He is about 5 years old, adores every person he meets and loves to cuddle. We would love to see him in a home where he can be the center of someone's world and finally receive the unconditional love he has been longing for. If you would like to meet Mason please call or email us so we can set up a time. 
Because we require home checks and Masons ongoing medical needs a foster or adopter should be within 30 minutes of Santa Clarita, Ca.

Dusty hit the trail for reasons known only to him and wound up at the shelter as a lost dog on Jan. 8; his family did not come to find him. He is about 2 years old and weighs 51 pounds. He is up-to-date on vaccinations, now neutered, heartworm tested negative and will be microchipped upon adoption. Come meet him in Run 835 using ID#626787.

Please note, all of the pet listings on Friends of Shelter Animals for Cobb are done by volunteers, not shelter staff. If this pet came in as lost (not an owner surrender), we don't know how they might be with children, other pets, or if house trained. You can bring your pet to the shelter for a meet & greet with your potential new best friend. When calling the shelter about a cat or dog, please use THE ID NUMBER, names are oftentimes made up by volunteers. 

This pet and many others are available for adoption from the Cobb County Animal Shelter 1060 Al Bishop Dr. Marietta, GA 30008, call (770) 499-4136 for more information. Shelter hours are: Tues. - Sun. 10:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. by appointment only until further notice, CLOSED Mondays & Holidays.

animal.description:
Can you believe that Razoo has been available for adoption for over 500 days?! It blows my mind because this boy is the absolute sweetest dog you’ll ever meet. He wiggles his whole body when he sees a new person, puts his slender head in your hand, and stares lovingly at you with his big brown eyes. He has nothing but love to share! He likes hanging out with other dogs, big and small, but much prefers the company of his people. He will be your shadow who follows you everywhere you go.
 
Razoo lived a tough life before being rescued. It was evident that he had been abused and bears a big white scar on his head as proof. He is so thankful to the people that worked with him to overcome some of his fears. He still gets nervous getting into cars and being out and about in the world. He is definitely a homebody! Razoo knows how to sit and shake. He is also kennel trained and potty trained. He is extremely treat motivated and will work for food or affection. 

Razoo is a 5-6 year old Greyhound/Doberman/Great Dane mix and weighs about 80lbs. He is being fostered in Fort Worth, TX through Fort Worth Abandoned Animal Alliance. 

Submit your application here:
https://form.jotform.com/81144515117146

animal.description:
After a very hard life, Sunny is looking for her perfect forever home! This brown-eyed girl is low maintenance and very deserving. She can be shy sometimes but also enjoys hanging out in the living areas with her people. She is never too far away from her canine companions and would benefit from another calm dog in the home. She walks well on a leash and likes to explore outside. She enjoys running around in the yard from time to time, but always comes in to cuddle up in a cozy bed. She is a quiet girl that will win over your heart in an instant. Sunny looks forward to her bright future with an understanding and patient adopter who will love her for the rest of her life. 

Sunny lived in a hoarding house for her whole life. For the last couple of years, the dogs lived alone and continued to reproduce resulting in a whopping 43 dogs residing in the home by themselves. She was rescued by Satterwhite Pets before coming to us! Sunny is an 8 year old 35lb mixed breed being fostered in Fort Worth, TX. 

Sunny is heartworm positive. The cost of her treatment is paid for by the rescue. She has already started her treatment and will just need to go to her vet appointments in Fort Worth to complete it (three visits total).

Majestic Mando is a stunning, mostly black husky with one blue and one brown eye behind his black mask. He is a sweet, 1 year-old boy who is a typical high-energy husky, and seeks love, attention, reassurance, and a stable, loving home.

Due to unfortunate circumstances, Mando recently lost his family. He is timid at 1st but once he warms up he is confident and excited to go for hikes, walks, & play. He is house trained, good on a leash, somewhat crate trained, and great with children of all ages.
Mando appears to be a dominant male so may do better with another submissive male or a female.

Mando is looking for a husky savvy family or foster family who can continue positive training, daily exercise, stimulation, and good nutrition. Mando is micro chipped and up to date on vaccines and spayed.  His adoption fee is $400  Minimum adoption age is 25 and no apartments/ condos .

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.If interested in any of our animals for adoption, or to foster an animal, please fill out the respective application here to get the process started. Visit our FAQ webpage for commonly asked questions about our adoption/foster process.
My name is Deejay. I was living in a crate in a pole barn when my foster family met me. I'm very playful and very, very smart! I've learned lots of tricks already! I settle down nicely and love to cuddle. Im looking for a home with no kids or pets because I would love to be your one and only. I will be best with a fence so I can run. A rural area without the hustle bustle of city life would be wonderful. I am currently on meds for some anxiety and will need to work with an in person trainer when one is available.

I am looking for an active home who can burn my energy. I know my forever home is out there. Could that be with you? If so, please fill out an online appication.

Last Day Dog Rescue now microchips all animals before adoption. Microchips are implanted between the animals shoulder blades and are a permanent form of identification. The microchips are registered to Last Day Dog Rescue with the adopter's info added once adopted. If the animal is ever lost and slips his/her collar/tags the microchip allows the finder to know who to contact if scanned for a microchip. Animals MUST still have a collar with tags on at all times. Per our contract, we take all our animals back if for any reason you can't keep your adopted animal.

Please understand the statements about this animal are based upon the foster home's evaluation of the animal. The animal might behave differently (negatively or positively) in your home. While the animal might be good with the current foster's dogs, cats, children, etc., it may not be with your animal(s) or children. The animal may be housebroken or litter trained in the home of the foster but may relapse in your home. The animal is represented to the public as it performs in the foster home and any statements made regarding the animal are conditional to that foster home setting. Please understand that statements made regarding this animal are simply overviews and are not guaranteed.

The Petfinder.com system requires that we choose a predominant breed or breed mix for our animals. Visual breed identification in animals is unreliable so for most of the animals we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each animal as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our animals based on personality, not by breed label.

Thank you for looking through our list of animals needing forever homes and choosing rescue first. We appreciate you stopping by.

animal.description:
Meet Lady! Behind those adorable eyes is a sad story to tell, but she's living in the moment and is a great pet! Lady came into rescue after her person passed away from cancer. He was an animal lover and when he passed there were seven living together - Prince, Lady, Daisy, Bo, Roscoe, Brutus, and Max. They are not bonded to one another but enjoy the company of other pets and so far, all have tested great with cats, (respectful) kids, and all adults. They appear housetrained, crate trained or crate tolerant, and enjoy some snuggles on or near your lap! Lady could use a dental procedure and prefers canned food over hard kibble, but she's been great in foster care and is a perfect pet. Because we are foster based, we require an approved application because a meet and greet can be scheduled. We think that is fair to our foster and the pet so every meet and greet has the potential to result in an immediate adoption! The application is available on the rescue website and can be completed online. We work with many rescues and strive to find every rescued dog in our care a great home. Sometimes that means transferring that pet to another location where adoption may be more likely. We currently have partners in New York, Pennsylvania, and Vermont.

If you are interesting in meeting any of our pets, the process is to complete an application. It can be downloaded as a pdf document from our website and submitted by email to WindyRidgeRescue@gmail.com as a scanned document or as photos OR can be completed entirely online. Both links are in the header of our website.

Because we are foster based, we require an approved application to schedule a meet and greet. We feel that is fair to our fosters and rescues so every meet and greet can result in an adoption.

We do not have set adoption fees for dogs, but hope adopters will donate generously so we can rescue more. The medical care for every dog can easily exceed the adoption donation. Average adoption fees for dogs in the area range from $175 up to $450.

We ask for a minimum adoption donation of $50 for cats regardless of age. Each cat is up to date on vaccinations, dewormer, and microchipped. Larger donations are always welcome so we can rescue more. Medical care for each cat easily exceeds the minimum donation.

As with every rescue, our resources are limited and the need for rescue help is unlimited. Your generosity helps us to rescue more.

Adopting or fostering for a rescue frees up a space where a new rescue can reside.

If you can't adopt or foster, than please consider donating.
animal.name: Lady - Loving & Cuddly!

animal.description: Meet Keyla! This sweet girl is only about 1 year old and looks to be a Shepherd mix. She has been around kids and other dogs and done well with both. Keyla loves going to Fiesta Island and is a social, friendly girl. She does like to chase kitties though so needs a home with no cats. Keyla is good on leash and is learning her basic commands. She loves to play with toys and get attention from her people. She knows how to use a dog door and is housetrained in her current foster home. If you think you are ready to add to your family by adopting Keyla, then fill out an adoption application on our website today! We recommend completing the application process and connecting with a adoption coach before looking for a dog or puppy you'd like to adopt. If you're already approved to adopt or if you've adopted from Labs and More before, connect with your adoption coach for the next steps. Your interest in adopting a rescued dog or puppy from Labs and More Rescue is appreciated! Please find our adoption information at www.labsandmore.org. Your adoption donation provides funding for Labs and More, a nonprofit organization which is supported solely by Volunteers and funded by donations. Good news is your adoption donation can be considered tax deductible. So much care is provided to your new dog prior to the adoption, including: spay and neuter, microchip, veterinarian visit(s), vaccinations, and other medical care as needed. Many of the dogs we rescue require extensive surgeries and care prior to adoption. Please understand we are unable to predict future behavior or medical needs of your adopted dog. We provide no guarantees regarding behavior, breed, or age of the dogs. Thank you for rescuing.Thank you for looking to Adopt a Labrador Retriever or other Mixed Breed Dog from California Labradors Retrievers and More Rescue. Please take a moment and go to www.labsandmore.org and click on Adopt to complete our online dog adoption application. If you have any questions email us at doginfo@labsandmore.org or call us at 858-273-5386. Thank you for looking to a rescue group to fulfill your dream of adding a new dog to your life! Dogs + Love = Family

animal.description:
Breed: Mastiff/Pit Bull mix
Sex: Female
DOB: ~01/06/2013
Weight: 68 lbs
Energy Level: Medium
Personality Type: Goofy, Sweet, Outgoing, Talkative
History: Transferred from animal control
Good With: Kids, Cats, Dogs
Ideal Home: Just about any home! Apartments could be ok with an active family!
Fence Requirements: Not required.
Special Info:

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the dog might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications per pet at this time! Please follow the rules below to ensure your application is reviewed; pay attention closely to these instructions because applications will NOT be processed if they are not followed. Please keep in mind that dog/cat availability is currently changing by the hour; you will receive an email if the animal you are interested in is no longer available. New dogs become available almost every day, so feel free to let us know if someone else interests you if your initial choice is already adopted! 

Fill out the application (DOG: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IHD-DOG-Application-9-10-18.pdf, CAT: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/IHD-CAT-Application.pdf) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed. If you are going to type your responses, open the application, save it, type your answers, and save it again. 

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 dog/cat that you are interested in. If there are multiple dogs/cats, number them in order of priority. 

-Scan a copy of proof of home ownership (i.e. tax bill, deed, or mortgage payment - you can black out the account #, etc.) or animal clause/agreement of your rental agreement.

-Attach the application and home ownership proof/rental agreement animal clause to a new email and send it to bark@iheartdogs.org. The subject line must be formatted to read ""#1 choice of dog/cat, Your First and Last Name"". Example: Subject: Fido, Jane Doe
Once your application is received, it will be assigned to an Adoption Counselor who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other dogs/cats. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 45 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot.

-We will continue to perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Home visits will be in person for the yard and virtual for inside the home.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

While this process may seem cumbersome, it is interim during COVID-19, and it is designed to help us respond to the volume of emails we receive every day. Since we are receiving a high volume of applications, please be patient if a dog/cat is no longer available. 

Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
Missy is a fiercely loyal girl who is very loving to her person once she has a chance to warm up and feel comfortable. She is a bulky cattle dog mix of sorts, weighing in at around 50#. Missy loves to follow her foster mom around the house and yard, making sure she's safe and close. Missy is good with other easy going dogs who respect boundaries and that generally mind their business. Missy is a simple, low-energy girl who requires only a safe and relaxing space to be her best self. 

Missy prefers a calm and consistent environment and would prefer a home with little to no traffic. A chaotic home with lots of activity or foot traffic makes her very uncomfortable and would not be a good fit. Missy is great in her crate and will require one in her adoptive home- this provides her a safe place to relax and feel secure. Missy is great about using the dog door to hang out in the yard but will need further training and time to master her leash skills. Missy would not do well in an apartment type setting and will require a fully fenced yard for her to do her business as she pleases. 

Her ideal home would be calm, consistent and secure. She would greatly benefit from a strong and confident handler that would give her the appropriate time to become comfortable and feel safe in her home, while providing some basic training, gentle exposure, positive reinforcement, and consistent structure. 

Do you have a calm and respectful home that Missy might fit in well with? She is a sweet and loyal girl who would love to give companionship to someone who can give her time to warm up and settle in. 

Missy is fixed, vaccinated and microchipped. Her adoption fee is $200. To be considered, please first apply online at caws.org. If you are interested in adopting a CAWS pet, please fill out an online application at https://caws.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Sweet little Dottie is the happiest and sweetest little gal! She is a mature little 9 lb chihuahua mix of sorts, loves to lounge on the couch, in her bed (or yours) and to hang around at your feet, giving little gentle kisses at any opportunity! She gets along fine with the other easy going dogs and cats in her foster home. Dottie loves everyone she meets and quickly makes fast friends. 

She loves to lounge, chew on bones and follow her people around, laying quietly at their feet. Dottie is crate trained and very much enjoys the retreat of her crate when unattended and to privately eat her twice daily, portioned meals. She would love to go for daily walks and is really great about staying close. She is also great about using the dog door in her foster home. Dottie is a respectful and quiet gal who rarely barks, only making silly sounds during feeding time.

Dottie is fixed, vaccinated, microchipped and healthy! . 

Her adoption fee is $100. To be considered, please start by applying online at caws.org. 

Please note that we carefully select adoptive homes that best fit the needs of the animals in our care and not on a first come, first serve basis. Thanks! If you are interested in adopting a CAWS pet, please fill out an online application at https://caws.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Raven is currently in boarding looking for a foster or foster to adopt home. She takes a few minutes to warm up to someone new, but then is a playful and active girl, She is looking for someone to help her work on her manners, general obedience and jumping behaviors. She has lived with both large and tiny dogs. Young kids are not recommended due to her size and exuberance. ----
For more information email mitliebegsdr@gmail.com or fill out an application on our website www.mlgsdr.com

*Disclaimer, we're providing what information we know and what has been passed along by previous owners, shelters, etc. If the information you're looking for is not listed, please reach out and request more detail.

All dogs/puppies have been fully vetted including spay/neuter, micro-chipping, worming, heartworm testing, and preventative treatment, and all required age appropriate vaccinations. As required by Wisconsin Act 90, all dogs will have received a veterinarian exam (CVI) within the past 30 days, prior to finalizing the adoption. We reserve the right to not adopt to homes with children under the age of 7 years old. We also offer free beginner obedience classes (in Green Bay, WI) for any dog adopted from us.

We always recommend crate training, exercise, playtime and a regular schedule for potty breaks when bringing a new dog into your home. Adjustment takes time for both you and your new family member, so remember to be patient.


Mit Liebe German Shepherd Dog Rescue License #272376-DS

animal.description:
This energetic girl will have you dancing in the RAIN!

Hello guys! My name is Rain, but I am a dollop of sunshine! I am a 3 year old, female, spayed, Cattle dog-American bulldog mix. I am 65 lbs of love and a good girl at that! I am house trained and have learned to heel beautifully on leash with a Gentle Leader. The Animal Pad and my foster parents scooped me up from the Humane Society where I was brought in as a stray. They have been my guiding angels through tough times and I cannot wait to find my forever home!

I am a really sweet girl, and live for my people with utmost loyalty and love! My foster parents say I have no concept of personal space. I mean, when I can sit on your lap and give you kisses, why not? I love our early morning cuddles and I'm happiest sleeping in bed with you! A good game of fetch or keep away always gets me going. And I LIVE for tug of war! I'll even bring you a toy and leave one side in your lap to grab. I'm a total smartie and pick up training so fast, I love the mental stimulation and making my people proud of me! I wag my tail like no tomorrow when praised for 'sitting' so well instead of barking! I have a whole bunch of energy, and I will always be up for some runs and hikes. I can get anxious if I am separated from my people, but my foster parents make me practice sleeping alone at night and I'm doing well with that. I may be rough on the edges, but a diamond shines the brightest after it's polished.

I bond quickly and adore my people! I may be a big girl but inside I'm a big baby, and would love to have someone around to show me the ropes with structure and exercise. I get along well with my foster dog sibling and it took us about 2 days to get here. I struggled with reactivity for a while, getting overly excited and barking and lunging at new dogs or strange sights or noises. I've mostly kicked this bad habit, but I'll need my new family to continue to remind me to be calm when things are triggering around me. I am super playful with my new foster sis though, and play-wrestling is so fun! I don't mind sharing food, toys and treats too. Socialization to new situations is definitely helpful! About kids, my energy could be a bit much for them, but being around older teens who can play as well as guide me might be okay. I am not a huge fan of cats, and would rather not live with them.

I would do best in an adult-only family, or with older teenagers, with a strong-leader like parent who can take me on fun, outdoor adventures and have amazing playdates in a yard. Since I'm super smart I'd like to keep busy with mental stimulation games and learn lots more tricks! My parent should have a confident personality, with experience working with big dogs who need an alpha. With proper introduction, I would enjoy living with another well-balanced, playful dog sibling. But it would also be fine for me to be the only pet in the home for a while, to get attention and time for obedience training and socialization. My adoption fee is $300 and that includes spaying/neutering, shots, and microchip. If you want to take me home, please fill out the form on the website here https://theanimalpad.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Requirements for adoption;
*Needs another YOUNG, friendly small dog to live with
*okay with cats
*no children
*quiet home needed
*no apartments/rented rooms
*must have attached yard 

My name is Fozzie. You will not believe how far I’ve come by just looking at my pictures so please read my description carefully. I was living in a yard with another doggie friend,  never allowed inside, until one day my owner decided he didn’t want us in the yard either. So out on the streets we went! 
I was living on the streets for months, evading all the neighbors that tried catching me. I had never known a loving hand so I was very scared and shut down. Finally, a nice lady from this rescue was able to catch me, and that’s when things really began to change. I was taken to the vet and they shaved off all my dirty mats. They said a am about 2 years old. I went to a home and realized how much I love cuddling on the couch with the other dogs and playing with them too! My favorite time of the day is feeding time, or anytime that involves food.  My foster mom tells me all the time how brave I am because I am still learning to trust people, and have made good strides in my foster home, but I am still VERY leery and scared of new people. I am crate trained and doing very well with my house training. I walk ok leash but I still need help with my confidence.  My world was a scary place, and I am working hard to put the past behind me. I need to live with other small dog(s) who are good natured and can continue to show me the ropes and maybe even like to play with me.  My perfect owner would be someone who has a quiet demeanor and lots of time and patience to help me continue healing my heart and gaining trust in the world around me. 
Noisy and/or busy households are too much for me to handle...and kids can be very scary for me too, so my new home should not have children. 
My adoption fee is $450 which includes health examination, current vaccinations, neuter, microchip, flea and deworming treatment along with any other medical or dental deemed necessary by our veterinarian.

Starla is silly, sleek, & single -- finally! She came to rescue from a municipal shelter where she & her 9 (yes, nine!) little pups had been brought as strays. Life as a rescue dog has rocked, but Starla is done being a mom & ready to find a new furever family of her very own.

Starla is okay with most other dogs, but would request she be the only dog (if possible). She prefers her canine playmates active, but NOT bossy or otherwise likely to clash with Starla's status as "Queen Bee". People of all types are awesome, but if kids are in the picture.... older, school age humans are best (young kids might get accidentally knocked over). A family cat or small furry pet is likely to trigger her hunting hound side, so Starla is seeking a furever family without those please.

Starla is crate trained, house-trained, & knows how to use a doggie door! Being a young VERY athletic girl, Starla will do best in an active home who has a securely fenced yard... or is willing to 110% commit to regular daily leash walking/running so she can work out all her happy wiggles. Bonus points if you have any stuffy toys or dental chews to share?

If you think Starla is the dog for you, please fill out an adoption application today!

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
STARLA i
s available for adoption through K-9 Rescue of the Eastern Shore.

An adoption process is required to include filling out an online adoption application available at the following link -- https://www.k9rescuees.org/info/adoption

Veterinary and personal reference checks, and a home visit/meet-n-greet are required PRIOR to being approved to adopt. The time frame for completing this process depends largely on how quickly references respond, your vet office is able to speak to us (some want written permission first), your landlord or HOA (if applicable) confirms their approval for a pet, & how your schedule aligns with that of our volunteer(s) for the Home Visit
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

animal.description:
Piyo initially came to animal control as a stray that was never reclaimed.  He weighs about 9 pounds and is estimated to be 3-4 years old.  Once we had him home, we noticed that Piyo held up his left rear leg occasionally when he runs.  The vet determined after x-rays that his hip was probably injured when he was very young and was never treated.  He does very well with a inexpensive daily medication that is chewable and he takes it as a treat after breakfast.   It is possible that he may need hip surgery some day in his future if the medication is not enough to ease his pain.

Piyo is such a sweet little man with a very shiny, soft coat that is non-shedding.  He's shy at first and will take a while to feel safe.  He may well have been passed around and is just not sure of his place and what is going to happen.

He's completely housebroken and may have had a doggie door.  He's been trustworthy in the house but if food is involved, he is on high alert.  He loves to play tag and wrestle with the other dogs his size.  He will entertain himself with his bone or a toy.  Piyo is a champion snuggler and will charge up onto the bed and dive under the covers.  So, guess what, he's been sleeping in my bed.  He snuggles as close as he can and doesn't move all night.  My feet have been very happy!

This boy is such a happy and gentle soul who just wants to be with his person.  He does bark, however, at noises and strangers outside so no apartments or condos for him.

Piyo has been neutered, vaccinated, microchipped and tested for heartworms.  His adoption fee is $300.00.

If you are interested in adopting Piyo, please write us at PricelessPoochRescue@gmail.com and ask for an application to adopt.  We are a foster-home based organization, and Piyo is in a foster home in Atlanta.  The adoption process starts when you submit your application.  Once that has been approved, we will contact you to schedule a time for you to meet us.

Name: Teny
Breeds: Pit Bull Mix
Age: Young Adult
Gender: Female

Minnesota, Teny is arriving and is very excited to meet you! This compact pitty girl is the happiest creature you will meet, and she has an exuberance for life that is unmatched. She found herself in the shelter in Alabama after being found as a stray, but is ready for a home of her own. She is a sweet girl and is good with other dogs, though we have not seen her with kitties yet. Her perfect home would be one that has a fenced yard so she can show you her zoomies and have some area to play with you. After which it will certainly require some cuddles on the couch and watching some TV. This girl is arriving to Minnesota on 2/6 and is ready for her adopters to pick her up that day to begin the 2 week trial. She is heartworm positive and has started on the treatment regimen. She will need to be treated with the injections at our vet after she arrives. 

Teny was positive for heartworm disease and will be treated by our vets after she arrives. More information on heartworm and treatment can be found here: http://headinghomek9rescue.com/Heartworm.pdf

Requirements: Home with yard space.

Adoption Fee: $450 + tax. This includes neuter/spay, current vaccinations as age appropriate, heartworm/tick testing if appropriate, deworming, microchip, and current preventatives

Interested in adopting?  Fill out a preadopt application here: https://form.jotform.com/203104997748162

animal.description:
Name: Teny
Breeds: Pit Bull Mix
Age: Young Adult
Gender: Female

Minnesota, Teny is arriving and is very excited to meet you! This compact pitty girl is the happiest creature you will meet, and she has an exuberance for life that is unmatched. She found herself in the shelter in Alabama after being found as a stray, but is ready for a home of her own. She is a sweet girl and is good with other dogs, though we have not seen her with kitties yet. Her perfect home would be one that has a fenced yard so she can show you her zoomies and have some area to play with you. After which it will certainly require some cuddles on the couch and watching some TV. This girl is arriving to Minnesota on 2/6 and is ready for her adopters to pick her up that day to begin the 2 week trial. She is heartworm positive and has started on the treatment regimen. She will need to be treated with the injections at our vet after she arrives. 

Teny was positive for heartworm disease and will be treated by our vets after she arrives. More information on heartworm and treatment can be found here: http://headinghomek9rescue.com/Heartworm.pdf

Requirements: Home with yard space.

Adoption Fee: $450 + tax. This includes neuter/spay, current vaccinations as age appropriate, heartworm/tick testing if appropriate, deworming, microchip, and current preventatives

Interested in adopting?  Fill out a preadopt application here: https://form.jotform.com/203104997748162

You can email fostersheadinghomek9@gmail.com with additional questions.

animal.description:
Think outside the lines
Giggle til you weep
Puppies are the greatest fun
And cuddle in their sleep!

It’s not all straight and narrow
Lots of wiggle waggle 
Puppies do it different
Like children’s Scribble Scrabble. 

Meet Tulip!  She is one of 11 puppies born to Aspen. She was born in foster care and has been loved and well cared for from the moment she entered this world. Her Mommy and Daddy were both strays that were found together in Millington, TN. She is a typical puppy!  Playful, bouncy, energetic, curious, always starving, and quite simply adorable. She loves attention, playing with toys, and loves meeting new people. The toy basket, hugs and treats are the favs with this litter. She is working on crate training and housebreaking.  She is learning how to walk on a leash, but with all puppies, will need continued training, consistency, patience and lots and lots of love.  The weather has been really cold for a young puppy to be outside often for leash training and we are extremely careful to not expose young puppies to unsafe areas until they are fully vaccinated. She plays well with other dogs, but has not been formally cat tested. She is a bit excitable about the kitties, so we have just been able to do fence greetings at this time.  Puppies require a lot of time, training and effort, so please only apply if you have all of that and lots of love to give. We will not adopt if you are not home or have someone lined up to let her out and spend time with her while you are at work. 

If this pup sparks your interest, Then jump in line and apply!  Our app is on the home page, This puppy is gonna fly!

ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:   Tulip
Breed:  Black Mouth Cur mix
Gender:  Female
Age:  almost 3 months
Weight: 12 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Will be 1/22/2021

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with other dogs of various sizes, genders and breeds

We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. We are all volunteers that work full-time jobs, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.

Breeds: Boxer/Bulldog Mix
Age: Young Adult
Gender: Female

Jada is a sweet, young adult. Boxer mix that was found as a stray with horrible skin. Thankfully she went to a shelter where she could get the care she needed, and nobody showed up to save her. She is so thankful for the care she is receiving and she is just a lovely dog. Her past of neglect is behind her and she is ready for a home that will take appropriate care of her. Her hair continues to grow back in with good nutrition and medications, but it may not be perfect by the time she arrives. We do know she is good with other dogs and interested but not mean about kitties. She has been great with all the people at the shelter. She is Heartworm positive and has started the pre-medication prior to the injections to kill the worms. This treatment is covered by the rescue at our vets. She arrives to Minnesota on 2/6 and is looking for an adopter to step up and take her that day to begin the 2 week trial to make sure she is a good match.

Jada was positive for heartworm disease and will be treated by our vets after she arrives. More information on heartworm and treatment can be found here: http://headinghomek9rescue.com/Heartworm.pdf

animal.description:
*BEEFCAKE ALERT*

REQUIREMENTS:
FENCED IN YARD
NO SMALL DOGS (due to size)
NO CATS
KIDS 12 YEARS AND OLDER
DOG SAVVY PARENT
ADOPTION APPLICATION: www.misfitangelsrescue.org

*Wayne is one adorable hunk! He is around 4yrs old (Est. DOB: 12/4/16) & is 86lbs. He has put on needed-weight since coming to Misfits, & could stand to fill out even more (his ideal/end weight will likely be between 90-100lbs). Wayne was pulled from Saginaw County Animal Care & Control, after just completing heartworm treatment. 
*He definitely did not know how to “dog” at first… but now, he is a total delight! He LOVES his people, & loves being near them. He has learned manners & does a great job at coming when called, sitting, waiting when asked, & does not jump up (which for his size, is much appreciated.) He is working on his leash manners, & is housebroken/crate trained. Wayne now loves the Idea of going buh-bye…but still has reservations about climbing into some vehicles. Once he is in there though, he’s a smiley happy fella! 
*Wayne would love if his people were home more often than not…someone that works a 7-8 hour+ day will not work for this big guy. He has decided that 4-6 hours is the max that he wants to be without someone, & the max amount of time without going outside/potty. 
*Due to his size & the fact that he has a new lease on life, we recommend a home with older children (12yrs old+), as well as no cats or small dogs (under 20lbs.) Wayne has been good with medium to large sized dogs, & is working on his socialization with them daily. He has been around a small dog with no issue, but due to his happy-feet & size, he could unintentionally hurt a little dog. His ideal doggy companion (if he must have one) would be mostly calm, & probably 5yrs old+. He does well running around & romping with dogs, but things are still new & acclimating to a home with a current dog will take patience & time to ensure it goes as smooth as possible. 
*Wayne is neutered, current on vaccinations, microchipped, Heartworm negative & current on monthly preventions. He is big-headed, adorable gentleman that would love a forever home to call his own!
ADOPTION APPLICATION:  WWW.MISFITANGELSRESCUE.ORG

animal.description:
Our girl Faun is about three years old, but she's just as active as a pup. Very outgoing personality, she loves going on leashed walks. Faun will climb chain link so she's going to need a solid, 6' wooden fence to keep her safe.
She is affectionate and smart, loves kids and is good with other dogs. We are going to recommend 'no cats' for this gal, she's a bit rowdy. She's perfect for an active family - and would excel in obedience class. She is very sociable and loves being with others.All of our dogs are available for a $200 donation. This includes them being spayed/neutered, micro-chipped, and fully vaccinated.
To adopt a dog, we require an approved pre-application, as well as a securely fenced yard. This means an actual, physical, fence. 'Invisible' fences are not acceptable, sorry. If you live in an apartment and do not have a yard, we are not able to adopt to you.
Please contact us at: dogtownmutts@gmail.com for details.
Please note: we typically do not do 'out of the area' adoptions. This would be any location more than 60 miles away from the Reno/Carson City area.

animal.description:
Think outside the lines
Giggle til you weep
Puppies are the greatest fun
And cuddle in their sleep!

It’s not all straight and narrow
Lots of wiggle waggle 
Puppies do it different
Like children’s Scribble Scrabble. 

Meet Alder!  He is one of 11 puppies born to Aspen. He was born in foster care and has been loved and well cared for from the moment he entered this world. His Mommy and Daddy were both strays that were found together in Millington, TN. He is a typical puppy!  Playful, bouncy, energetic, curious, always starving, and quite simply adorable. He loves attention, playing with toys, and loves meeting new people. The toy basket, hugs and treats are the favs with this litter. He is working on crate training and housebreaking.  He is learning how to walk on a leash, but with all puppies, will need continued training, consistency, patience and lots and lots of love.  The weather has been really cold for a young puppy to be outside often for leash training and we are extremely careful to not expose young puppies to unsafe areas until they are fully vaccinated. He plays well with other dogs, but has not been formally cat tested. He is a bit excitable about the kitties, so we have just been able to do fence greetings at this time.  Puppies require a lot of time, training and effort, so please only apply if you have all of that and lots of love to give. We will not adopt if you are not home or have someone lined up to let him out and spend time with him while you are at work. 

If this pup sparks your interest, Then jump in line and apply!  Our app is on the home page, This puppy is gonna fly!

ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:   Alder
Breed:  Black Mouth Cur mix
Gender:  Male
Age:  almost 3 months
Weight: 12 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Will be 1/22/2021
Vaccines: Current
Heartworm:  Too Young, currently on Heartgard
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with other dogs of various sizes, genders and breeds
Cats:   Yes. He has met cats, but will need a slow meet and greet since he is puppy excitable. Recommend proper intro and supervision. 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, he has met middle age children and has done well. He has not been tested with infants or toddlers. He is excitable and bouncy at times, and could potentially knock a little one down or get under feet.

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers that work full-time jobs, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

animal.description:
Roscoe is so chill! He has such a sad story to share, but he's living in the moment and is a great pet! He has been crated without issue during the workday and is very sweet and attentive when you are home. He walks great on a leash or listens well even off leash. He was in a foster home with an 8 year old and 1 year old and did well. He came into rescue after his person passed away from cancer. He was an animal lover and when he passed there were seven living together - Prince, Lady, Daisy, Bo, Roscoe, Brutus, and Max. They are not bonded to one another but enjoy the company of other pets and so far, all have tested great with cats, (respectful) kids, and all adults. They appear housetrained, crate trained or crate tolerant, and enjoy some snuggles on or near your lap! Roscoe did test positive for heartworm disease, but the rescue will provide items to complete treatment. Because we are foster based, we require an approved application because a meet and greet can be scheduled. We think that is fair to our foster and the pet so every meet and greet has the potential to result in an immediate adoption! The application is available on the rescue website and can be completed online. We work with many rescues and strive to find every rescued dog in our care a great home. Sometimes that means transferring that pet to another location where adoption may be more likely. We currently have partners in New York, Pennsylvania, and Vermont.

If you are interesting in meeting any of our pets, the process is to complete an application. It can be downloaded as a pdf document from our website and submitted by email to WindyRidgeRescue@gmail.com as a scanned document or as photos OR can be completed entirely online. Both links are in the header of our website.

Because we are foster based, we require an approved application to schedule a meet and greet. We feel that is fair to our fosters and rescues so every meet and greet can result in an adoption.

We do not have set adoption fees for dogs, but hope adopters will donate generously so we can rescue more. The medical care for every dog can easily exceed the adoption donation. Average adoption fees for dogs in the area range from $175 up to $450.

We ask for a minimum adoption donation of $50 for cats regardless of age. Each cat is up to date on vaccinations, dewormer, and microchipped. Larger donations are always welcome so we can rescue more. Medical care for each cat easily exceeds the minimum donation.

As with every rescue, our resources are limited and the need for rescue help is unlimited. Your generosity helps us to rescue more.

Adopting or fostering for a rescue frees up a space where a new rescue can reside.

If you can't adopt or foster, than please consider donating.

animal.description:
Meet our super sweet girl
Lumi
!

This poor girl was dumped New Year's Eve. She was seen frantically searching for her pups, even approaching moving cars just see if they might be inside, but she could not find them. They no doubt were still with
Lumi
's "owners" waiting unknowingly to be sold. This is what happens in our city far too often!

Lumi
is only about a year to year and half old, bred at her first heat cycle then discarded like garbage.

She is surprisingly heartworm negative, now vaccinated and will be spayed as soon as she is healed enough to undergo surgery. She so deserves a home where she will be loved and cared for, and taught how to be the wonderful girl she wants to be. She is very smart and learns quickly. She also gets along with other dogs! She so wants a human to be happy with her.

If you are interested in fostering or adopting our adorable girl, please complete the appropriate application at
www.scoutshonor.org

Dior came to us with his brother Louis. They are 8 months old. Both were surrendered to a local animal control. They are sweet rambunctious young pups who we would love to see stay together. These dogs will need a fenced yard.  They do not like meeting other dogs when leashed and will bark and act ferocious.  Because they are still puppies, they need obedience training.  They have will chew on your arms when you pet them, so absolutely no children under the age of 10.

Alcovy dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on all vaccines, up to date on heart-worm preventative and flea preventative and micro-chipped.  Required registration of microchip in owner's name is $10.99.

If interested in adoption, please complete an online application on Alcovy Pet Rescue's website at www.alcovypet.com.  You must have a vet reference to adopt.  We verify the care of past/current pets.  Applications without a vet reference will not be approved for adoption.  Our goal is to have the very best home for all our dogs and cats and therefore we reserve the right to approve or deny an application based on what we determine is in the pet's best interest.

animal.description:
Lyle is a 7 month old husky mix (with what we aren't sure) who weighs 35 lbs.

He's good at going potty outside and can hold it as needed.

Crate trained and goes in easily.

Like a puppy he will steals things left on the floor so he needs chew toys always available.

He only barks when excited or is playing and to be let in from outside.  

Mostly sleeps in his crate but also likes the couch or a dog bed.

Every dog is a playmate to Lyle.

No cats for Lyle. Too much prey drive.

He's still learning to be comfortable with new people but has no aggression at all. A home without children is best. 

Pulls a bit when on the leash since he loves walks but can definitely learn!

Loves car rides and will put his nose out the window if allowed. Waits in the car nicely for brief periods when foster mom is running errands.

Commands known: "wipe your paws', "unhook" (from harness), working on "come/come on"

Likes: shoes, socks, slippers, paper, plush toys, squeaky and crinkle toys, rubber treat dispenser toys, chasing balls, nylabones, does enjoy pets and will lay next to foster mom when watching tv.  Could be a frisbee dog candidate.

Dislikes: garbage cans, messy yards, trash bags or any pile on the curb, driveways full of vehicles, and pick-up trucks.  He was rescued from a ghetto area after fending for himself on the street so Lyle is looking forward to living in a nice neighborhood. Who can blame him!

The best home for Lyle would be with a female owner who is a runner/outdoors and has a dog that needs a playmate. He will also thrive in a peaceful home environment. He needs a caring patient Mom and dog sibling who will help him blossom into a confident well socialized doggie. Lyle can be happy walking the same route every day but also does well venturing out to new greenbelts and nature areas. He needs a lot of patience with men as clearly they were not kind to him in his first months of life. Male dog whisperers can help doggies like Lyle learn to trust. Hopefully his forever Mom has a few around who are especially good with doggies.

Lyle has a beautiful prance when he's happy and its such a sight to see. He also really loves the snow! He loves running and has a look of sheer joy on his face when he runs. And he's a stunning pup who gets lots of compliments when he's out and about. 

He is neutered, microchipped, up to date on vaccines including rabies, heartworm negative and current on prevention.

There will be transport fees (varies upon arrangements made per discussion) in addition to the $300 adoption fee.

If you are interested in adopting Lyle, please complete an adoption application on https://www.westernaustralianshepherdrescue.com/.

He is young and energetic so would do best with a family that matches his energy. He likes and needs a job to do to stay busy. A well exercised hound is a good hound.

Tank is available to LOCAL ADOPTERS ONLY (within an hour drive of Middleburg, FL due to the training classes offered).

Cats are likely a No.

He needs a home that has a younger dog, his size or larger, that matches his energy level.

Adoption fee is $350.00

That includes the following vetting:

Distemper/parvo series

Leptosporosis Vaccines

Bordetella

Fecal exam

Rabies

Microchip

Neuter

Current on dewormer and prevention

Food to transition

Home visit and reference checks are REQUIRED and are NOT negotiable.

** Also includes 6 week group obedience class in Middleburg, FL.

We cannot adopt Tank to those living in an apartment, condo, townhouse or other attached housing. He is quite loud!

animal.description:
BONDED PAIR!
Misty and Ralph are at Satchel's waiting for their next and forever family to come and pick them. This lovable pair are happy-go-lucky, loving every minute of life despite what they have been through for the past year. They had a happy homelife until their person passed away and they found themselves in a loveless home, spending day after day in a small room with nothing to do, no windows to look out and no human companionship. Ralph loves squeaky toys, blankets, rugs to roll all over and treats. Misty loves to lounge around, snuggle with people and blankets. Both love people and are friendly with everyone they meet. They walk well on leash and enjoy running free in our large play yard. Although they don't mind spending some time alone, they are bonded and we often see them snuggling in the same crate. We are told that Ralph is likely 11-12 years old and Misty 9 years old but they do appear somewhat younger. If you're looking for a pair of bonded senior dogs, please consider meeting Misty and Ralph. Submit the adoption application (no commitment) found on our website, www.satchelslastresort.org, and adoption counselor will get back to you to set up an appointment.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Todd is a 3 year old breeder release from Missouri. Todd has settled in nicely with his foster pack and is a pretty laid back dog. He no longer howls due to anxiety and he's become quite the snuggler. He loves to play with his foster brother, he loves mealtime and he's walking like a champ with a leash and gentle leader. He's very gentle and submissive with my dogs and will now come to people for love/pets. He will need a family with a privacy fenced yard or a condo type scenario as he still likes to take adventures if not on leash and has an impressive vertical. He still has occasional accidents in the house if I'm not watching him, but he's amenable to keeping his diaper on in the house. His recall is improving and he's treat motivated so he should be easy to train. We are currently working on "sit" and "wait." He's a young dog eager to please and will make someone a wonderful pet!

Adoption fee includes: Full veterinary exam, alter, prepaid microchip, dewormed, Rabies vaccine, DAPP vaccine, Bordetella vaccine, 4DX

, flea/tick and heartworm preventative while in rescue. Adoption fee:

$395.00

animal.description:
Chuck is a classic Jack Russell Terrier but with the grace and wisdom that only comes with age. He lived with the same family for the first ten years of his life and came into our care after being surrendered to a Quebec shelter for behavioural and health issues. It took us a few weeks to understand Chuck’s particularities, but we think he is finally ready to find his perfect co-pilot. 

Chuck is a sweet, gentle, and whip-smart little guy. He is keen to learn and please his human friends. Although he is not a “velcro dog,” he does have extreme separation anxiety and cannot be crated or left alone for any period of time. Separation anxiety is extremely difficult to cure and we need to find Chuck a family who will understand that. It’s also important that his new family encourages healthy boundaries and rules to ensure it doesn’t escalate. 

Despite his age, Chuck loves to go for long walks and playtime. He displays leash reactivity when confronted with other dogs. His foster parents have been working on this behaviour and it’s important that his new family continues this training to help him enjoy his time outside without the anxiety he currently feels. Chuck requires the stimulation and bonding that walks around the neighbourhood provide. He is polite and friendly with new people, interested in chasing squirrels and pigeons, and is lovely around cats. 

With proper exercise, Chuck is calm and quiet in the home. He loves to make a little nest and snooze the afternoon away. He has excellent house manners, rarely barks, knows basic tricks and commands, and is potty trained. Chuck is currently being fostered in an apartment in a busy neighbourhood in downtown Toronto. He’s done very well in the car and is a gentleman in Ubers and on the TTC. 

Chuck has recently been diagnosed with a rare condition called diabetes insipidus (essentially, hormonal diabetes). The illness makes him drink water excessively and subsequently, pee excessively. Chuck has started medication to manage the symptoms and we are very much hoping they will resolve the issue. He will likely need these meds and regular vet visits for the rest of his life. We estimate the cost of his meds will be c. $40 a month.

Chuck is looking for a best friend to share adventures and the couch. He loves human affection and praise, thrives with positive reinforcement and a calm home environment. He really enjoys training and learning new commands… so I guess you CAN teach an old dog new tricks! Oh and if he could have a feline brother or sister he’d like that a lot too.

animal.description:
Lucy is a super sweet and affectionate Boxer/Staffy mix who is 5 years old and weighs 40 lbs. She came to BarkVille severely malnourished & underweight, but fortunately we were able to place her in a wonderful foster home where she is putting on healthy weight every day.  She loves food & treats and enjoys gobbling everything up as soon as she sees it!  She is a happy, quiet, calm, easy keeper who snorts & grunts like the adorable, little piggy she is!  She is a low energy girl who likes to play a little bit each day & loves chewing on her hard bones, but overall is very content to relax & chill with her family.  Her #1 requirement is a window that she can lay in front of to see outside because that is most definitely her favorite place to be!  Her foster mom says that Lucy is the ultimate companion ... very loving & attentive to whoever is near her.  She doesn't need a lot of exercise, but she enjoys going for walks (although her leash manners are still a work in progress).  She is very smart & eager to please and could be a great fit for a person/family looking for a loyal, devoted companion who doesn't need to be exercised daily.  Lucy can live happily in an apt/condo or a single family home with fenced yard.  She is perfectly house trained & crate trained, spayed, fully vaccinated & microchipped.  

To see more videos of this super cute girl, copy & paste these links into your browser ...

https://youtu.be/V66PYuJco-w
https://youtu.be/-GsyEUsrvzQ

For more information about the lovable miss Lucy, please email us at info@barkvilledogrescue.org. If you would like to adopt this sweet girl, please submit an application for her at https://www.barkvilledogrescue.org/applications

animal.description:
Hello my name is Roxie 
I am a two-year-old shepherd mix per my shelter paperwork and weigh 50.8 pounds. I have a very sad story and it touched the hearts of my rescue and they came and got me from the shelter. I was with my owner in Reidsville North Carolina when someone shot and killed him when we were walking. I didn’t know what to do so I guarded his body until the help arrived. These nice policemen came and picked me up and took me to the shelter where I had to stay from 10/16/20 until my rescue pulled me on 1/11/21 when I became available. I had to be held for investigation and I was so confused as to what happened to my person and what I had done wrong to be taken to a shelter. The ladies there gave me lots of love and attention and now I’m in a loving foster home waiting on someone to choose me. I am house trained dog friendly and do well with children. They do not know about cats since my foster does not have one. I just want a new home of my very own and people to love me and give me a safe home. What I went through was very traumatic and I do not want to lose another human that I love that way. If you think you are the right family and can love me forever, please contact my rescue for an adoption application. I promise to be a good girl and love you forever. 
Love 
Roxie

animal.description:
****Please do not message the rescue asking if this dog is still available; if a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO BEFORE EMAILING****

*Name: Sally
*Age: 7 years
*Current Weight: 45 pounds
*Rescued from: Texas
*Adoption fee: $375 (plus $125 spay/neuter deposit, which is refundable when spay/neuter agreement is fulfilled)
*Health: up to date on required vaccines

Sally has had a rough life, and we are looking for the perfect home for this girl.  Sally is good with other dogs, loves to explore outside and go for neighborhood walks.  She is great in a car and enjoys going for rides.  Sally is house broken,  crate trained, spayed, heartworm negative and UTD on her vaccines. Sally has learned to trust her foster mom but unfortunately, she continues to be fearful of her foster dad.  Sally probably needs an all female home and only older considerate kids.  Another canine sibling would be great for Sally and a fenced yard.   Sally shines bright and is such a loving dog when given the needed time to develop trust with her people.

To apply to adopt Sally, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. 

**Meet and greets will not be scheduled without an approved application.**


-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING
-------------------------------------------------------
**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

animal.description:
We are a non-profit and an all-volunteer organization. Our adoption fee is $295.  Please read this posting to answer most of your questions about me.

Hello  meet Pigglet a beautiful mix that was surrendered to the the Hope Fur Pets Rescue. Pigglet was found as a stray near one of the volunteers homes after posting and asking the neighbors in the area Pigglets owner decided to surrender to us as they couldn't care for him any longer. He is super sweet and appears to get along with other dogs as long as they are easy going, he prefers dogs his own size. He is super sweet and friendly to everyone he meets. We named him Pigglet because he does a lot of snorting like a pig. He is really gentle and doesn't jump up on you so he would be okay with smaller kids.  I'm all up to date on vet care appropriate for my age including heartworm prevention, spay/neuter, microchip and all vaccinations and ready to be the newest member of your home! 

Please fill out our application an application is required in order to be considered: copy the below text and paste it into your browser:  

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1K_84a3Y0wF0QbdYBz17b10Uwm4kAXxz-Y0Gx5HexZz0/edit

If you have any questions, please send an email to hopefurpets@gmail.com

Us fur-kids deserve a second chance. Thank you for supporting rescues who help ensure we get one! And please remember to spay and neuter your pets and neighborhood strays! While I was at the shelter, I couldn't believe all of the wonderful dogs, cats, puppies, and kittens who are homeless. Take it from me, being homeless is no fun!

Application is required. No member of our organization receives proceeds from our adoption fees.  All dogs have past experiences, preferences and personalities.  Please always consider the personality and breed tendencies of any pup that you are interested in adopting to ensure that he or she will be the perfect fit for your home, for both your sake and his!  Do not select a forever companion based on looks alone.  Make this home his or her home for life!

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please download and complete an Adoption Questionnaire from our website and email Michelle at mhunt@k-9lifesavers.org
You can learn about the adoption process and find a Word, PDF and ONLINE version of the questionnaire by visiting: http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/howtoadopt/.
Dog's Name: Eva
Estimated Breed : Miniature Pinscher Mix
Approximate Age: 1-2 years
Approximate Weight: approx. 30 lbs
Currently Living at: Boarding
Adoption Fee: $300
DOG'S DESCRIPTION
Do you like to be busy... well so does Eva! Eva is a very energetic, happy little gal hoping to find a home with lots of toys! She will need an active family with a fenced in back yard to so that she can run and play. Due to her high energy level, she will not be able to be placed in apt/condos. She is also not found of cats. Who wants some EVA LOVE?
Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.
Adoption fees cover basic vetting, spay/neuter surgery (for dogs over 6 months old), rabies, distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention and monthly flea/tick prevention (while the animal is in our care), and transport costs from high-kill shelter. Please note that on average, K-9 Lifesavers spend significantly more on each dog than their adoption fee. Adoption fee for HW positive dog also covers heartworm treatment at our partner vets.
Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org
Sponsor Me! Make a tax-deductible donation today by visiting us at http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/ . Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support!
For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.
Please "like" our Facebook Page for the most current events and new dogs.
Thank you for considering a rescue dog!

animal.description:
To access the home page for our group, click on Southern Comfort Maltese Rescue which will take you to the map page.  Below the map is our logo and the link to click on to access adoption forms, contact info or to donate. ALL DONATIONS ARE TAX DEDUCTIBLE.


Adoption Fee: $150.00 for both

 
These boys are looking for a forever home, they were not able to be cared for by their family and SCMR agreed to help them find a new home.They both have lost some of their house manners, but are working on that.  They are not liter mates, but are siblings from the same home.
 
Ozzy is a toy poodle, he is 12 years old and weighs 8 pounds, he is neutered, he is blind but will learn his space and loves to take lots of naps.  Ozzy loves to walk around confidently in the yard enjoying the smells and he is happy to let you know it's dinnertime with a woof or two.
 
Fozzie is a Maltese, is 14 years old, and weighs 6 pounds. He is neutered and very loving.    He loves to cuddle and is a true lap dog.   He hardly has any teeth, and is hard of hearing, but he responds to everything going on around him.
 
A NOTE FROM THE BOYS' FOSTER MOM:
 
Fozzie, the older of the two, pops around like a puppy.  He is petite and adorable.  I haven't seen any aggression in him at all.  Sometimes he "talks" in a soft growly voice, but he is not a barker.  He loves to sleep with me and cuddle.
 
Ozzie is younger but his blindness has slowed him down a bit.  He enjoys the yard and walks around happily picking up all the "messages" left by my other foster pups adding his own to them!  Unlike many dogs who lose their sight, he hasn't become fearful or nervous, and he dearly loves being held and talked to. Ozzie lets me know when it's time for breakfast and will complain if I'm too slow making dinner.  Neither have any special dietary needs, are not fussy, and not on any meds. They both wear belly bands in the house, but we all go out several times a day so they barely get wet.

They are located in Largo, FL loving life!!!.


NOTE: SCMR DOES NOT adopt to homes with children under the age of 10 years or homes with Electric Fences

Out-of-state adoptions are possible; however, the approved adoptive home is responsible for making the necessary arrangements to pick up their new little one.

animal.description:
Malcom and Bentley came to us as family surrenders following the death of their beloved guardian. This is what their guardian's sister has to say about them:

Malcolm and Bentley are a bonded pair and have been together since Bentley was adopted as a puppy at 7 weeks old. They must be kept together. I have known them since she brought them home; both are social dogs and good with people, kids and other dogs. Both are trained house dogs, are full of energy and need a fenced yard and space to run and/or regular walks. As much as it will break my heart to let these boys go, I have a very demanding job, travel frequently and do not have a large fenced yard that they are accustomed to. I am hoping to find someone who can give them regular attention who has a large yard for them to run or will be active with them and who hopefully wouldn't mind keeping in touch with me. They have been raised as part of the family.

Bentley is a 10 yr old black lab. I believe he is over 100 lbs of muscle; though he thinks he is a lap dog. He is very friendly and still has lots of energy to play and run. For the past 7-8 yrs he has had a large fenced yard to run in and I don't believe he has walked on a leash much so he could use some leash manners but he does respond to basic commands (Come, heal, sit, etc). He does like to chase wild animals so I would not let him (or Malcolm) run freely outside an enclosure just for their safety. I know my sister used to take him to the dog park when she was able to. He eats twice a day and usually gobbles down all his food when given. He does like to beg but will usually listen if you tell him to go lay down. I have not noticed him being a jumper. He is a big baby and likes lots of attention. Bently is currently on some maintenance meds/supplements (arthritis, allergies, joint health). Since he has been with me I have noticed his allergies (some itching and a hot spot on his front leg) but I would never have known he has arthritis. 

Malcolm is a 12 yr old Chesapeake Bay Retiever mix, guessing roughly 60 pounds. I know he passed therapy dog training and my sister used to take him to Verland to visit the residents there when she worked there years ago. I haven't been able to locate his certificate unfortunately. He is very docile and affectionate. He does like to bark when he hears the doorbell or sees someone walking down the street. He has much better leash manners than Bentley. Malcom has had allergies off and on but I have not noticed him having any issues since he has been with me. He does have a lipoma (benign fatty tumor) on his shoulder (visible in some of the pics) but does not seem to cause him any pain or other issues. He is in good health.

Both have beds, collars, leashes, bowls, toys, etc which can go with them.

If there is any other information I can provide please feel free to call me 412-266-4670.
animal.name: Bentley and Malcolm
